summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 29384, entitled: "An ordinance relating to regulating and licensing temporary public amusements, exhibitions and entertainment in the City of Seattle, providing penalties for violation thereof, and repealing all ordinances or parts of ordinances in conflict herewith", approved May 7, 1912, and Ordinance No. 29976, entitled; "An ordinance relating to theatres and other places of amusement and to the licensing, conduct or operation thereof, providing penalties for violation and repealing all ordinances or parts of ordinances in conflict herewith", approved September 4, 1912.
